	<!-- message -->
	<p>I was only in the EQ Develoment forum for the last hour, and apparently most of the ranged attack stuff was covered well before I got there.  I'll relate what I did hear though:<br />
<br />
The guy who was speaking (not sure what his name was) explained that as it was at the moment, mobs only have 60 spaces on their hate list.  The list drops people who are 150 feet or more away in favour of those people who are closeer to the mob.  So in effect what was happening was that casters and archers who were more than 150 feet away in a 60-person plus raid weren't on the hate list at all.  He said that they had increased the capacity of the hate list to incorporate all people doing damage, no matter whether they are 2 feet away or 200.<br />
<br />
That's pretty much all I heard on the archery front, though if anyone is interested in EQ2, I did post in the EQ2 forum about where Rangers stand as a class in the progression system <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" /></p>
	
	
	
		<div>__________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=58382" target="_blank">Huntress Mahgnillig Aubenwolf</a><br />
Grandmaster Fletcher (250)<br />
Grandmaster Fisherelf (200)<br />
<a href="http://www.phoenix-ascendant.org/" target="_blank">Phoenix Ascendant</a> of the 7th Hammer</div>
	
	
