	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Amise</b><br /><i>Removing the limit on the size of the hate list doesn't really scream nerf to me at all.   When meleeing sometimes it's prudent to jolt and/or turn off attack.  Archery shouldn't be any different.  Should they compensate us for time spent jolting while using melee weapons too?</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>The time we spent having to jolt while using melee weapons has something we've had to deal with since Kunark, and is already a factor in our melee DPS.  In some cases, this isn't even a problem, thanks to Jolting Blades.<br />
<br />
I'm not talking about this upcoming change of the hate list.  I'm sure it will affect us very little, since most of us don't draw aggro with archery in an XP group even when we're within 150 units of range.  I was addressing the comment "we need to be responsible for the damage we do." they keep using.  We maintain a certain DPS with archery the way it is.  The next "aggro change" coming down the pipeline will effectively lower our DPS if we have to spend time using aggro mitigation spells or turning off archery auto-attack to stay low on the hate list.  Some of you may be on board with letting Verant indirectly nerf our archery DPS, but I'm not. =P  This actually sounds like an indirect nerf to all ranged attack damage though... I'm surprised I haven't heard too many casters screaming about this one.  Maybe they don't understand their DPS will go down because they can't maintain their current DPS without pingponging a mob or getting summoned and walloped once the new "aggro change" goes in (not this hate list change).</p>
	
	
	
