	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Malvesti</b><br /><i>That's correct.  Scott Hartsman emphasized that Tuesday's change is only a change to the hate-list, allowing an unlimited number of people, rather than 60 currently.<br />
<br />
He implied that  LOS, agro, (and autoattack?) changes would be coming in the near future.<br />
<br />
He talked about the missile system that EQ uses (with respect to poofing arrows).  He said (as we know) bolt spells, arrows, and thrown weapons use it.  The arrows are very stupid while in flight and so if they get poofed by geometry, there's no way to trace the arrow back to the archer (so poofing arrows don't give a "miss" message).  He left the door open for a change to the missile system but gave no indication that any change was currently in the works.  The idea to take archery off the missile system and put it in the magic DD system was brought up and he was pretty hostile to it--though I think it was the first he had heard of the suggestion.<br />
<br />
He never gave the indication that he was hostile to archery at all.  There was absolutely no talk of "rangers do too much damage."  Basically his only concern was that if you do damage, you need to be responsible for it.<br />
<br />
He mentioned archery changes on PvP as we've all read--archery does 66% in PvP now and you're more likely to miss when moving.  He said that's ONLY PvP--that's not a future PvE change.<br />
<br />
<br />
I also was able to speak to Ryan (Butler?) in between sessions.  I told him that there is 1 best arrow in the game, and only Tunare followers can use it, and asked him whether he could take a look at that.    He told me that it was actually not the best arrow and there's a "few" (I think that's the word he used) arrows that have not been discovered yet.  But he also said he'd take a look at the diety issue on those crafted arrows.<br />
<br />
<br />
Hope this answers some of your questions.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Yay! So once again, they lied to us when they said that archery would be fixed if it was nerfed. I'm not surprised</p>
	
	
	
