	<p>From what I'm hearing here, this will not be a major change at all.  It is seldom in a raid situation that I shoot from greater than 150 feet, occasionally yes, but not that often.  Increasing the size of the hate list and increasing the distance we can gain agro from does not seem outrageous.  With a 200 range on Jolt line of spells, this does not seem unreasonable.<br />
<br />
Someone mentioned in an earlier threat that if you were looking at it from a story perspective, you would not expect a monster to leave the hacking of blades in his face to chase down an archer, but I suppose if you pissed him off enough, he might just come tramping through the bushes after you.  Okay, maybe a stretch, but it does make the game more intersting.<br />
<br />
As far as the rumor of new arrows, that's pretty exciting if it is true.  Mithral Champion Arrows are dropable, it could well be that the ones yet to be discovered are as well.  It's something to look forward to anyway.<br />
<br />
From what I'm hearing here, I'm not worried, mostly interested to see what the change brings.</p>
	
	
	
	
	
