	<td class="alt2" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Hmm... there's a flaw in the idea of making weapon proc imbue spells work with ranged attack and bows that I've noticed in my times of solo'ing.  My bow and arrows allow me to shoot a mob at one end of a HoH basement room all the way from pretty much the other side.  I use a Warmaster's Recurve Bow from Tallon Zek, which has a proc of Judgement of Ice.  I can shoot just fine from all the way across the room all I want, but when I reach a certain distance I'll start getting a "Your target is too far away" while I'm shooting it, which is telling me... "You are too far away for the proc on this bow to go off at effect this target..."<br />
<br />
So in other words, you'd probably have to be in range of a big ol AE mob, if that's what you're trying to avoid, for your proc of Jolt to go off... unless they increased the range of the spell, or if you had some Extended Range focus item, I'm assuming.</p>
	
	
	
