	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>Personally, it sounds to me like they are just making the two lists a mob maintains equivelent.  The aggro list is already unlimited as far as I recall, and if you engage a mob in anyway, you are on the list, until you die, it dies, you zone, or someone wipes the list.  This is the list that establishes Rampage.<br />
<br />
It sounds like their hate list though is still restricted like the aggro list used to be way back in the early days.  Instead of computing the amount of hate for everyone present, the hate list only keeps track of those within 150 units of the NPC, then orders them against the aggro list to determine who the NPC attacks.  If you are beyond the 150 units, you are still on the aggro list, you just aren't figured into the kill response.  However, once everyone within the 150 radii is dead, then the NPC starts working its way down the aggro list, based on distance.<br />
<br />
I wonder if this is related to the bug where if the puller (first aggro) is far enough away from the group, no one gets experience for the kill?</p>
	
	
	
