	<!-- message -->
	<p><blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" />Originally Posted by <b>Yendor</b><br /><i>The time we spent having to jolt while using melee weapons has something we've had to deal with since Kunark, and is already a factor in our melee DPS.  In some cases, this isn't even a problem, thanks to Jolting Blades.</i><hr size="1" /></blockquote>Just because something has been around a while doesn't make it right or reasonable and doesn't mean it's always gonna be that way.  I hate the arguement of "this is the status quo therefore it's the way it should always be", it's a pointless one to me.   Not being on the hate list due to range needs changing, so it's being changed.  <blockquote><span class="smallfont">Quote:</span><hr size="1" /><br />
 Some of you may be on board with letting Verant indirectly nerf our archery DPS, but I'm not. =P  <hr size="1" /></blockquote>This isn't a nerf.  This is nowhere near on a par with the changes in the aggro list still to come, and nowhere near on a par with the rumors of an EQ or AM nerf.  When there's a real nerf I'll start complaining, until then I'm not getting my panties twisted.<br />
<br />
Elsewhere someone mentioned the dependancy of Rangers on mana to decrease aggro.  I'm sorry but I am in a hurry and can't go back and find the quote. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />   Anyway, my point is, we are hybrids.  <i> Hybrids</i>!  With <i>spells</i> and <i>mana</i>.  Using a spell to decrease hate is not an unreasonable thing to me.  Sure, monks and rogues get a non-spell-based skill to reduce hate.  They don't have mana or spells.  My jolt works well when it lands.  It also has a partial effect when resisted.  Rogues and Monks don't have the benefit of their skills partially working when they fail.   Hide and FD also involve turning off attack and losing some DPS, just like Jolt involves losing some DPS.   I have never felt that Rangers are at a disadvantage by having a spell-based hate reducer.</p>
	
	
	
